	(34, NULL, 'Getting to Know OSHA', 'OC0001', 'This course is fantastic', 'This course is written for all employees of an organization. This course covers an overview of the Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA). OSHA is the U.S. agency established in 1970 within the Department of Labor to develop and enforce regulations for the safety and health of workers in businesses that are engaged in interstate commerce. Since we are all employees and deserve a safe and healthy work environment, it behooves each one of us to understand the agency that sets and enforces standards, provides training, outreach, and education to encourage continual process improvement in workplace safety and health. The information you take away from this course can assist you in the knowledge of your rights to work in a safe and healthy environment.', 1, 19, '', 0.50, 0, '2010-11-30 00:00:00', '2012-02-12 00:00:00', 1, 14, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<h1>\r\n	Appendix A</h1>\r\n<p>\r\n	Testing text&nbsp;Testing text&nbsp;Testing text&nbsp;Testing text&nbsp;Testing text&nbsp;Testing text&nbsp;Testing text&nbsp;Testing text&nbsp;Testing text&nbsp;Testing text&nbsp;Testing text&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 0, 1),
