	(36, NULL, 'Slip, Trip, and Fall Prevention', 'MS0123', 'This course is fantastic', 'This course is written for all individuals that are employed by healthcare organizations. This course is provided as part of a monthly safety education program that has the purpose of assisting employees in learning and understanding topics that will help prevent personal injuries, illnesses, and conditions. This course covers slip, trip, and fall (STF) prevention, which includes the top 10 hazards, explanations on how they contribute to STFs, the identification of where the top 10 hazards are likely to occur, and recommendations to reduce or eliminate STF hazards. This course is not intended to be an STF prevention program, however, it does provide guidance on creating and implementing one. By understanding the topics discussed in this course, you can better protect yourself and your fellow employees.', 1, 30, NULL, 0.50, 0, '2013-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, 0, 16, 0, 0, 1, 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 1);
